## рҹ’ә Entity: Seat (THE CRITICAL ONE!)

### Why Seat is Critical
- **SeatCategory** tells you the TYPE (VIP/Premium/Regular)
- **Seat** is the ACTUAL BOOKABLE UNIT with its own state

### Attributes
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| seat_id | UUID | Unique identifier |
| row | String | Row label (A, B, C...) |
| number | int | Seat number in row |
| category | SeatCategory | VIP/PREMIUM/REGULAR |
| status | SeatStatus | AVAILABLE/LOCKED/BOOKED |
| locked_by | User | Who locked it (None if not locked) |
| locked_until | DateTime | When lock expires (None if not locked) |
| booked_by | User | Who booked it (None if not booked) |

### Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `is_available()` | Check if status == AVAILABLE |
| `lock(user, duration)` | Set status to LOCKED, set timer |
| `unlock()` | Reset to AVAILABLE, clear lock info |
| `book(user)` | Set status to BOOKED |
| `release()` | Set back to AVAILABLE (on cancel) |

